🧱 1. Build only your swarm packages
cd ~/ros2_humble
colcon build --packages-up-to swarm_gazebo --symlink-install
🔌 2. Source ROS + your workspace
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
source ~/ros2_humble/install/setup.bash
🚀 3. Launch multi-robot simulation
ros2 launch swarm_gazebo multi_spawn.launch.py
🔍 4. Verify robots exist (optional)
ros2 topic list | grep robot
ros2 node list




Goals (Best next path
1. Clean up the robot interface

Right now each robot works, but the setup is still a bit rough. Make it cleaner by giving each robot:

odometry topic
scan topic
cmd_vel
a clear robot name / namespace

That makes later mapping and navigation much easier.

2. Add RViz visibility

You want to actually see what each robot sees.

Next, get:

one robot’s lidar visible in RViz
then all robots
maybe robot poses too

That helps a lot before SLAM.

3. Do SLAM with one robot first

Before true swarm exploration, make robot1 build a map.

That means:

robot1 + lidar + odometry
SLAM toolbox
map visible in RViz

This is the most important next milestone.

4. Save the map

Once one robot can map the environment, save it and confirm you can reload it.

Then you have:

exploration world
robot
reusable map
5. Add navigation to goals

After mapping, make one robot go to selected goals.

Then the behavior becomes:

map
choose target
move there
avoid obstacles while navigating
6. Only then scale to multi-robot exploration

After one robot works well:

robot2 and robot3 also get scan + odom
each explores
later share information or divide areas)